article.description: — Rayshon Harrison's 21 points helped Grand Canyon defeat Utah Valley 86-67 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Harrison's 21 lead Grand Canyon over Utah Valley 86-67
article.linkText: Harrison's 21 lead Grand Canyon over Utah Valley 86-67
article.story: OREM, Utah -- — Rayshon Harrison's 21 points helped Grand Canyon defeat Utah Valley 86-67 on Saturday night. Harrison was 7 of 14 shooting, including 3 for 5 from 3-point range, and went 4 for 4 from the line for the Antelopes (21-2, 11-1 Western Athletic Conference). Gabe McGlothan scored 17 points while shooting 5 for 8 (2 for 3 from 3-point range) and 5 of 6 from the free throw line, and added 11 rebounds. Tyon Grant-Foster was 3 of 13 shooting, including 1 for 3 from 3-point range, and went 7 for 8 from the line to finish with 14 points, while adding nine rebounds and four steals. Caleb Stone-Carrawell led the Wolverines (9-13, 4-7) in scoring, finishing with 15 points and six rebounds. Tanner Toolson added 14 points for Utah Valley. In addition, Trevin Dorius had 12 points, nine rebounds and five blocks. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
